The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for compressing graphs while preserving distances between terminal vertices. This topic is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
